race.comment: The well-related RARE MOON (7) (half to G3 winner Icarian Dream) showed good early speed and raced just off the lead before lifting to score by 1.5 lengths over 1400m at Gatton last start. In fine form and worth following up. LIFE OF TREE (1) recorded a gutsy maiden victory last time out over 1540m at Gold Coast Poly, scoring by a head. Looks well placed and he is one of the main chances. BATTLESPACE (5) was in the firing line on the turn and finished second last time over 1600m at Gatton, beaten a long neck. Improving with racing and can run a bold race. SO YOU CAN TORQUE (11) put in an improved performance last time out and may earn some minor money.
